[{"title":"ʯͷ������","url":"/2025/05/15/石头剪刀布/","content":"\n```\n#include <stdio.h>\n#include <stdint.h>\n#include <time.h>\n#include <stdlib.h>\n \n#define u32 uint32_t\n#define ROCK 1\n#define PAPER 2\n#define SCISSORS 3\n \nvoid destemine_winner(u32 player_move, u32 computer_move)\n{\n\t//�����ų�ƽ�ֵ����\n\tif (player_move == computer_move) {\n\t\tputs(\"ƽ�֣�\");\n\t\treturn;\n\t}\n \n\t//����һ��ʤ���Ĺ���ӳ�䣬���м�����ҵ��ƶ���ֵ������ƶ����Դ�ܼ�������ƶ�\n \n\tu32 winning_moves[4] = { 0, SCISSORS, ROCK, PAPER };\n\t//0��ռλ��\n \n\t//winning_moves[1] SCISSORS\n\t//ROCK == 1\n\t//PAPER == 2\n\t//SCISSORS == 3\n\t\n\t//����player_move����ҵ��ƶ���winning_moves[player_move]����ǿ��Դ�ܼ�������ƶ�\n\t//����˵���ѡ1��ֻ�е������ѡ3ʱ�Ż��䣬��ô�ͽ�winning_moves�е�winning_moves[1]����λ3\n\tif (computer_move == winning_moves[player_move]) {\n\t\tputs(\"��Ӯ�ˣ�\");\n\t}\n\telse {\n\t\tputs(\"�����ˣ�\");\n\t}\n}\n \nu32 get_player_choice() {\n\tu32 choice;\n\tputs(\"��ѡ��1��ʯͷ��2�ǲ���3�Ǽ���\");\n\tscanf_s(\"%d\", &choice);\n \n\twhile (choice < ROCK || choice > SCISSORS) {\n\t\tputs(\"��Чѡ��������ѡ��1��ʯͷ��2�ǲ���3�Ǽ���\");\n\t\tscanf_s(\"%d\", &choice);\n\t}\n \n\treturn choice;\n}\n \nu32 get_computer_choice() {\n\treturn (rand() % (SCISSORS - ROCK + 1)) + ROCK;\n}\n \nvoid print_instructions() {\n \n\tputs(\"ʯͷ~����~������Ϸ��ʼ��\");\n\tputs(\"�����������֣�ȷ����ȭ��1��ʯͷ��2�ǲ���3�Ǽ���\");\n\tputs(\"==========================================\");\n}\nvoid print_choice(u32 choice) {\n\tswitch (choice)\n\t{\n\tcase ROCK: puts(\"ʯͷ\"); break;\n\tcase PAPER: puts(\"��\"); break;\n\tcase SCISSORS: puts(\"����\"); break;\n\t}\n}\n \nint main(void)\n{\n\t//��ʼ�������������\n\tsrand(time(NULL));\n \n\t//��ӡ��Ϸ˵��\n\tprint_instructions();\n \n\t//��ȡ��Һͼ������ѡ��\n\tu32 player_choice = get_player_choice();\n\tu32 computer_choice = get_computer_choice();\n \n\t//չʾ��Һͼ�������ѡ��\n\tputs(\"��ѡ����\");\n\tprint_choice(player_choice);\n\tputs(\"�����ѡ����\");\n\tprint_choice(computer_choice);\n \n\t//�ж�ȷ��Ӯ�ң�����չʾ\n\tdestemine_winner(player_choice, computer_choice);\n \n\treturn 0;\n}\n```","tags":["game"]},{"title":"hello","url":"/2025/05/11/hello/"},{"title":"Hello World","url":"/2025/05/11/hello-world/","content":"Welcome to [Hexo](https://hexo.io/)! This is your very first post. Check [documentation](https://hexo.io/docs/) for more info. If you get any problems when using Hexo, you can find the answer in [troubleshooting](https://hexo.io/docs/troubleshooting.html) or you can ask me on [GitHub](https://github.com/hexojs/hexo/issues).\n\n## Quick Start\n\n### Create a new post\n\n``` bash\n$ hexo new \"My New Post\"\n```\n\nMore info: [Writing](https://hexo.io/docs/writing.html)\n\n### Run server\n\n``` bash\n$ hexo server\n```\n\nMore info: [Server](https://hexo.io/docs/server.html)\n\n### Generate static files\n\n``` bash\n$ hexo generate\n```\n\nMore info: [Generating](https://hexo.io/docs/generating.html)\n\n### Deploy to remote sites\n\n``` bash\n$ hexo deploy\n```\n\nMore info: [Deployment](https://hexo.io/docs/one-command-deployment.html)\n"}]